pma:database.name: bookstore
pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `book_user_buy` ( `IDU` int(11) NOT NULL, `IDB` int(11) NOT NULL, `buy_date` datetime DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`IDU`,`IDB`), KEY `Bbuy_FK_idx` (`IDB`), CONSTRAINT `Bbuy_FK` FOREIGN KEY (`IDB`) REFERENCES `books` (`idb`), CONSTRAINT `Ubuy_FK` FOREIGN KEY (`IDU`) REFERENCES `users` (`idu`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci;
pma:database.pma:procedure: CREATE DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` PROCEDURE `add_buy`(in _IDB int, _IDU int) BEGIN INSERT INTO buy (IDB, IDU, buy_time, cost) SELECT IDB, _IDU, now(), cast(books.price-books.price*user_sale(_IDU) as decimal(9,2)) as "sale" FROM books WHERE IDB=_IDB; END

CREATE DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` PROCEDURE `popular_from_first_buy`() BEGIN SELECT books.IDB, title, book_count FROM ( SELECT IDB, count(book_user_buy.IDB) AS book_count FROM book_user_buy INNER JOIN ( SELECT IDU, min(buy_date) as buy_date FROM book_user_buy GROUP BY IDU ) as a ON a.IDU = book_user_buy.IDU AND a.buy_date = book_user_buy.buy_date GROUP BY IDB ) AS b INNER JOIN books ON b.IDB = books.IDB WHERE book_count = ( SELECT max(book_count) FROM ( SELECT IDB, count(book_user_buy.IDB) as book_count FROM book_user_buy INNER JOIN ( SELECT IDU, min(buy_date) as buy_date FROM book_user_buy GROUP BY IDU ) as a ON a.IDU = book_user_buy.IDU AND a.buy_date = book_user_buy.buy_date GROUP BY IDB ) as c ) ; END
